Last year throwback cuz now it’s like -35 all week.🥶☃️ Fun things for if you don’t live in da North that might surprise you…❄️
- when I was a kid in Fort McMurray: spitting outside and it turn to ice before it hit the snow
- frozen hair and eyelashes ❄️
- having to play outside at school recess if it is -20 or ‘warmer’
- NO snow days. At least in Alberta.(Late for work cuz ur car is stuck in the snow? Get a cab then or get fired..)
- waiting to defrost car / possibility of car not starting
- walking to work on icy sidewalks hoping you don’t slip and die at least of embarrassment
- every winter in Alberta when we try to be positive we think “at least there’s no huge spiders, snakes or RATS, hurricanes, tsunamis etc..🤷‍♀️
- “Tobogganing” and almost dying on crazy carpets
- tennis courts turn into hockey rinks in the winter.
.

Blood on their hands
Repressed Soul
Manmade Gods
The Hypocrisy of Humans
(Poem & painting by myself)🎨
.
Beautiful ladies surround the dining table in celebration of the feast they harvested. Taking the life of their gods’ creation but will ignorance and praying make it any better? The lady with gold hair and blue blazer seems to be the only one in distraught but goes with it anyways, because everyone else is doing it. Perhaps her fake god will save her?
.
A poem to go with it:
.
“Pray before the death upon the table
Your faith will not save you
Judge your fellow neighbour
because you’re holier than thou

Your wrathful Gods demand a sacrifice
“Give up your Life for me!”
Keep it up your whole life and you’ll never be free.”
.
So I ask, Why love one and eat the other?”🌱
.

Part 1 - Throwback of three years ago, That was just 3 weeks into my Germany trip.😵‍💫😍 most of these are in my highlights, but I thought I would make a trendy reel.🇩🇪 it seems like just yesterday, travelled there alone, one way ticket, for a concert, ended up going to more concerts, getting more tattoos, met people, did more than I thought, and stayed longer! ..,
.
Still to this day I am still sort of over the whole travelling thing, I got quite satisfied there. 😅 what with planes and luggage stuff ugh… but a wonderful and exciting experience, would definitely do it again.🖤
.
Would recommend solo traveling, you can choose whatever you want to do, even have a chill, relaxing, nothing days, and also meet people if you wish. Yes, it is indeed scary especially as a young woman and when you are not as familiar with the language, but you just have to not smile, look scary (meaning walk not so feminine lol. Sad but it is true and helpful anywhere if you don’t want to be harassed) and walk like you know where you’re going!!!.. no matter what time of day or night!! Trust me, it works! I realize I am slightly privileged in that I am white, but still as an attractive lady and with quite wild, not normal hair, perhaps lol what helps to navigate unseen waters alone is acting more rugged, you know like wiping your nose and coughing, and “acting as if” you are a local!😆 Ask yourself, what would make you not want to approach someone and do that!.,, to my surprise, most people thought I was from there and asked me for directions sometimes lol.

Tarot card reading in the forest today🍃 We have the Temperance card, short explanation of some important things about it I can say in under a minute, well it’s about balance and moderation yes and that seems boring but there is much more! It’s quite an interesting energy reminding you that you are protected by angels with the wings..🪽and reminding that you are in control of your life, in this physical world but also a spiritual being who can create your own reality, not in that you can control others or circumstances…but you can control how you react and think…
.
ALSO this Angel homie is also mixing energies ⚡️(Alchemy!) and using what he got to create something new. Real life example is using your talent and creativity to turn into money..
.
Of course the seemingly boring part of this card is moderation, people always think of like drinking or consuming less.. but you can replace bad habits with something even better. Why does moderation mean something awful?? OR some people think “your vegan don’t you miss ___??” Or that you have to sacrifice some things… but it is actually way better because I still eat good tasting foods and I feel much better!! So is it really a sacrifice or was it a wonderful investment in my health, well-being and happiness as well as doing less harm?? 🌱👊🏼 
.
Another example, people think they have to eat less to lose weight or whatever, ok but you can literally eat as much veggies, fruit and whole foods and not need to restrict because we are herbivores and thrive on whole foods, high in carbs, high in energy!🌱⚡️⚡️⚡️ Anyways card of the day!🥰 I actually have a video featured on my YouTube channel “Seitana Tarot” with this card featured and some balance yoga poses / class too if you want to check it out.🎥 Link in bio as usual.

High thots💭 I had written the other day about the law of polarity, mixing the physical and spiritual together to create a life worth living or meaning and fun.🖤💜I think that’s what makes life interesting. 
.
The law of polarity states that everything is and isn’t at the same time 🤔 and everything is dual. (The Kybalion - Hermetic philosophy is a great book if you’re like wtf she talking about now, then I’d recommend)😄 A good example is LOVE and HATE. Different? Yes but also similar in that they are very passionate emotions! If you have had a hater on the interwebs, they hate but also love you as they are watching your every move 👀 lol, obsession of any kind, praising or hating is not really that healthy… strong love or hate towards another is a passionate emotion that triggers something in you that you love about yourself (love) or dislike about your own self (hate). That’s just an example. Of course love makes you feel better though.🩷 Can love, or feeling good really be a “sin?” Or are we all one in the same anyway? … Anyways, focus on love and feeling good and you can’t go wrong..💜
.
I like to mix sexuality with spirituality which in this world seem like a strange and not right combination but really… one without the other is what is strange and not right, makes one go crazy in fact! Example: Obsessed woth $ex or p0rn / obsessed with praying/meditating all day are both unhealthy.. balance is 🔑 you know!
